Plot: Woodstock recounts the "3-days of peace and music" in the rural Bethel Hills area of upstate New York August, 1969 to an estimated 400,000 concert viewers. A series of vivid testimonials depicts the conditions, people and rock bands present during the event. To fully understand Woodstock, the 60s revolution, anti-war protesting and the counter culture in America the producers exploit candid film making and inside documentary interviews with those that participated.

Starring: Joen Baez, Canned Heat, Country Joe & The Fish, C, S & N, The Who, Ten Years After Jimi Hendrix, Joe Cocker, Arlo Guthrie, Santana, Jefferson Airplane, Bill Graham, Sly Stone, Richie Havens and more.
